{"id": 28, "ts": 1778757169.3441625, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "I\u2019ve gathered the remaining pieces of information that were still missing:\n* **Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 No one has any data on his teamwork or communication skills, but we do know he \u201cresponds to unexpected events adequately,\u201d concentrates very well, solves problems extremely well, and takes responsibility seriously. These traits point to strong reliability, calmness under pressure, and sound decision\u2011making, all critical for long\u2011haul operations. The only negatives are that he is described as moody and a loner, with no concrete evidence that this impairs crew interaction.\n* **Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 We still lack any information on how he handles stress or makes decisions under pressure. While he anticipates dangerous situations, sees complex connections, has excellent spatial vision, and shows very good leadership, his unfriendly demeanor and unhealthy eating habits raise concerns about crew morale and personal health on long flights.\n* **Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 He is very conscientious, handles stress well, assesses weather effectively, and has excellent computer skills. However, the disclosed weak memory for numbers is a direct safety risk for the many calculations required on long\u2011distance routes, and his pretentious attitude and occasional wrong tone could undermine crew cohesion.\n* **Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 He makes quick, correct decisions, puts others\u2019 concerns first, and creates a positive atmosphere with his crew, indicating good teamwork. Yet he has difficulty communicating ideas, is regarded as egocentric, and is not very willing to pursue further education\u2014factors that could hinder both crew coordination and long\u2011term professional development.\nGiven the evidence, Candidate\u202fD offers the most robust combination of reliability, technical competence, calmness under pressure, and responsibility. The interpersonal drawbacks (moody, loner) are not substantiated as safety\u2011critical, whereas the other candidates each have a more concrete deficiency that directly impacts flight safety or crew performance.\n**Vote:** Candidate\u202fD\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate D\"}"}
